```

## Key Conventions

### General
- **TypeScript everywhere**: all code (client and server) must be written in TypeScript with strict mode enabled — no plain `.js` files, no `any` unless absolutely unavoidable
- **Documentation lookup**: always use the **Context7 MCP** (`resolve-library-id` → `get-library-docs`) to fetch up-to-date documentation before using or advising on any library, framework, or tool — even well-known ones (Next.js, React, Prisma, Tailwind, Express, Zod, etc.)

### Backend
- **Modular structure**: each feature lives in `server/src/modules/<feature>/` with `service` and `validation` files; **routes** may be one or more routers (e.g. `exercise.routes.ts`, `folder.routes.ts`) mounted from `app.ts` under `/api/<segment>`
- **Validation**: Zod schemas validate request bodies via `validate()` middleware
- **Error handling**: throw `AppError` subclasses (`ConflictError`, `UnauthorizedError`) — caught by global `errorHandler`; `ZodError` → 400 with `details` (Zod 4 exposes issues on `err.issues`, not `errors`)
- **Health**: `GET /api/health` — lightweight status JSON for uptime checks
- **Email (invitations)**: `server/src/lib/mail.ts` — Nodemailer SMTP from env (`SMTP_HOST`, `SMTP_PORT`, `SMTP_USER`, `SMTP_PASS`, optional `SMTP_SECURE`, `MAIL_FROM`). When fully configured, `POST /api/admin/invite` sends the register link after creating the row; response always includes `inviteLink` plus `emailSent` / `emailError` for the UI. `CLIENT_URL` builds the invite URL (same origin the user should open in the browser)
- **Auth**: Better Auth handles `/api/auth/*` via `toNodeHandler`; protected routes use `authenticate` middleware which reads the session cookie via `auth.api.getSession()`; `req.user` is `{ instructorId, email, role }`; feature routes mount at `/api/<module>` (e.g. `/api/exercises`, `/api/admin`)
- **Public registration helpers**: `app.ts` exposes `/api/signup-status` and `/api/invite/verify` (query `token`) for the register page; invitation creation and listing live under `/api/admin/*`
- **Admin plugin**: Better Auth admin plugin (`defaultRole: "INSTRUCTOR"`, `adminRole: "ADMIN"`) provides `/api/auth/admin/*` endpoints (listUsers, banUser, unbanUser, setRole); custom admin routes at `/api/admin/*` use `authenticate` + `requireAdmin` middleware
- **Roles**: `Role` enum (`ADMIN` | `INSTRUCTOR`); default is `INSTRUCTOR`; admin guard via `requireAdmin` middleware
- **Prisma**: client imported from `src/lib/prisma.ts`; generated output at `src/generated/prisma`
- **Soft deletes**: `deletedAt` field on applicable models; soft-deleting an exercise also removes its Cloudinary assets and `ExerciseImage` rows
- **Image uploads (hybrid flow)**: images are uploaded to Cloudinary `temp/` folder via `POST /api/uploads/temp` (multer, 5 MB limit, JPEG/PNG/WebP); on exercise create/update, `publicIds[]` in the request body triggers promotion from `temp/` to `exercises/<exerciseId>/` via `cloudinary.uploader.rename` with UUID-based collision-resistant naming and all-or-nothing compensation; `DELETE /api/uploads/temp/:publicId` removes temp images; `PATCH /api/exercises/:id/images/reorder` reorders saved images; an hourly `node-cron` job deletes temp images older than 6 hours
- **Express type augmentation**: `server/src/types/express.d.ts` adds `imagePublicIds?: string[]` to `Request` via declaration merging; an inline middleware in exercise routes extracts `publicIds` from the body before Zod validation so schemas stay unchanged
- **Exercise progressions**: `Exercise.progressionOfId` points to an easier variation (self-referential FK). Service walks backward to root then forward for a linear chain. **`GET /api/exercises/:id/progression-chain`** returns `{ id, name, level }[]` from root to harder steps. **`PATCH /api/exercises/:id/progression`** body `{ progressionOfId: string | null }` updates only progression; **`POST/PATCH /api/exercises`** accept optional `progressionOfId` on create/update (Zod in `exercise.validation.ts`). Cycle prevention is enforced in **`ExerciseForm`** / **`ExerciseFormMultistep`** on edit (blocked parent IDs from the chain); consider hardening in the service if API clients multiply.
- **Exercise layers**: `ExerciseLayer` model stores ordered content blocks (`order`, `content`, `isFinisher`) per exercise; create/update endpoints accept `layers: { content, order?, isFinisher? }[]` — service replaces all layers atomically via `deleteMany` + `createMany`
- **Dropdown options API**: `server/src/modules/dropdowns/` — **`GET /api/dropdowns/:categoryKey`** returns options (global + instructor-specific) for a category; **`POST /api/dropdowns/:categoryKey`** creates an instructor-scoped custom option. `server/prisma/seed.ts` seeds categories with keys: `orientation`, `direction_faced`, `movement_type`, `equipment`, `machine_setup`, `spinal_movement`, `chain_type`, `joint_loading`, `class_type`, `class_style`
- **Extended exercise fields**: `Exercise` has optional string fields: `orientation`, `directionFaced`, `movementType`, `springs`, `machineSetup`, `transitionCues`, `cueing`; **`equipment`** and **`chainType`** are `String[]` (multiselect, default `[]`); **`spinalMovement`** and **`jointLoading`** are `String[]`; optional **`progressionNotes`** and **`regressionNotes`** (`String?`) for in-exercise progression/regression copy. Form uses dropdowns, checkboxes, and text inputs; detail page renders array fields as badges where applicable
- **Exercise list API**: **`GET /api/exercises`** — optional query **`page`** (≥ 1) and **`limit`** (1–100, default 24). When **`page`** is present, response is **`{ exercises, total, page, limit }`**; when **`page`** is omitted, response remains a **JSON array** of exercises (same shape as before) so callers like the class-plan **exercise picker** can load the full set without pagination. Zod: `listExercisesQuerySchema` in **`exercise.validation.ts`**
- **Class plan list API**: **`GET /api/class-plans`** — always paginated: **`{ data, total, page, limit }`** with defaults **`page=1`**, **`limit=20`** (client library uses **`CLASS_PLAN_LIBRARY_PAGE_SIZE`** / **`listClassPlans`**). Query filters: **`search`**, **`folderId`** (use **`none`** for unassigned), **`classType`**, **`classStyle`**, **`tags`** (comma-separated for `hasSome`). Zod: **`listClassPlansSchema`** in **`class-plan.validation.ts`**
- **Pagination design note — exercise list dual response**: One **`GET /api/exercises`** route, **two shapes** on purpose. **Paginated** (query includes **`page`**) → **`{ exercises, total, page, limit }`** — used by **`/exercises`** via **`exerciseApi.getExerciseListPage`** and **`useExerciseList`**. **Unpaginated** (omit **`page`**) → JSON **array** — used by **`exercise-picker-dialog.tsx`** via **`exerciseApi.getExercises`** so the picker can search/filter over the full matching set without stitching pages. If the multistep **progression-of** parent **`Select`** is re-enabled, it would use **`getExercises`** again (see comment in **`exercise-form-multistep.tsx`**). **`GET /api/class-plans`** does **not** use this pattern: responses are **always** **`{ data, total, page, limit }`** because template listing is library-only (no equivalent "load every row" picker on that list API). **Naming**: paginated exercise rows live under **`exercises`**; class plans use **`data`** — both include **`total`**, **`page`**, **`limit`**.

### Frontend
- **"use client"** directive on interactive pages and layout components
- **Auth gate**: `AppLayout` redirects unauthenticated users to `/login`; `AuthProvider` wraps Better Auth's `useSession()` hook
- **App shell**: `AppLayout` renders `Sidebar` + scrollable `main` only (no top bar). **Sidebar** — fixed mobile menu button; drawer on small screens, rail on `md+`; nav links in a scrollable middle; **account menu pinned to the bottom** (`DropdownMenu`, opens upward) with avatar, name/email, and **Log out** (`useAuth().logout` then `router.replace("/login")`). **Main** uses `p-4 pt-14` on small screens so content clears the hamburger; `md:p-6 md:pt-6` from `md` up.
- **Auth client**: `authClient` from `@/lib/auth-client` — provides `signIn.email()`, `signUp.email()`, `signOut()`, `useSession()`, plus `admin.*` methods via `adminClient` plugin
- **Roles**: `useAuth()` exposes `isAdmin` boolean and `instructor.role`; sidebar conditionally renders admin navigation; admin routes under `(dashboard)/admin/` have a layout guard redirecting non-admins
- **Path alias**: `@/*` maps to `./src/*`
- **Forms**: use **React Hook Form** with **`zodResolver`** from `@hookform/resolvers/zod` — `useForm({ resolver: zodResolver(schema), ... })` and Zod schemas under **`@/lib/validation/*`** (`auth-schemas.ts` for **`/login`**, **`/register`**, and **admin invite** via **`adminInviteFormSchema`**; **`exercise-form-schema.ts`** + **`buildExerciseFormDefaults`** for **`ExerciseForm`** and **`ExerciseFormMultistep`**); align with server Zod where practical. **`ExerciseFormMultistep`** (`exercise-form-multistep.tsx`): optional **`exercise?: Exercise`** — create without prop, edit with loaded exercise; same **`exerciseApi`** save path as single-page form; **`useDropdownOptions`**, folders, images; stepped **`trigger(STEP_FIELD_GROUPS)`** on **Continue**; step tabs jump without per-tab validation; **`onFormSubmit`** blocks native submit until final step; **`handleSubmit`** **`onInvalid`** toast + jump to first step with errors. **`ExerciseForm`** (single-page): **`useFieldArray`** for `layers`, **`Controller`** for shadcn **`Select`** and **`BulletTextarea`**, **`register`** / **`useWatch`** / **`setValue`** / **`getValues`**; image list (dropzone, reorder, temp `publicIds`) in **local React state** outside RHF; **`reset`** when `exercise?.id` changes on edit; **`embedInClassPlan`** + callbacks for class-plan dialogs. **Admin invite** (`admin/users/page.tsx` dialog): same stack — **`Controller`** + shadcn **`Select`** for role, **`register`** for email, inline **`errors.*`** + **`aria-invalid`** / **`border-destructive`** like exercise form fields.
- **UI components**: use **shadcn/ui** for all UI primitives and patterns that shadcn provides; import from `@/components/ui/*`. Build feature-specific composites under `components/<feature>/` (and `components/layout/`, `components/auth/`) rather than reimplementing primitives inline
- **Theming / colors**: prefer shadcn **semantic tokens** (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `text-destructive`, `border-border`, `bg-card`, `bg-primary/10`, etc.) over hardcoded Tailwind palette utilities (e.g. `bg-gray-900`, `text-red-500`) so light/dark and theme tweaks stay consistent
- **Component layout**: shell in `components/layout/`; dashboard in `components/dashboard/`; scheduling in `components/scheduling/`; auth in `components/auth/`; domain UI in `components/<domain>/`; shared hooks in `hooks/`

### UI & UX

Product brand in UI copy: **Layered.** (see `app/layout.tsx` metadata). Match existing polished surfaces (week overview, calendar, auth, library headers) when adding pages.

#### Visual language (dashboard & feature pages)

- **Page shells**: major views use `rounded-3xl border border-border bg-card shadow-lg` (or `shadow-sm` for nested panels); section headers often pair a **rounded-2xl icon tile** (`size-11`, `bg-primary/10 text-primary`) with `font-heading` title (`tracking-[-0.02em]`) and `text-sm text-muted-foreground` subtitle
- **Spacing**: outer page `space-y-6`; card padding `px-4 py-5 md:px-6 md:py-6`; nested lists `space-y-2`
- **Interactive rows/cards**: `rounded-2xl border`, hover `-translate-y-px` and/or `hover:shadow-md`, `focus-visible:ring-3 focus-visible:ring-ring/50`; use **`cursor-pointer`** on clickable calendar grid cells and event blocks (not default cursor)
- **Primary actions**: prefer `Button` with `rounded-full` on dialogs and auth; outline/secondary for secondary nav (e.g. week chevrons, filter chips)
- **Empty states**: dashed border panel (`border-dashed border-border/80 bg-muted/15`), centered icon in `rounded-2xl` tile, short title + helper text + one clear CTA
- **Loading**: centered spinner (`border-2 border-primary border-t-transparent`) or skeleton blocks inside the same card shell — do not leave a bare white area

#### Form controls (`@/lib/form-control-styles.ts`)

- **Single source of truth** for input, textarea, select trigger, date/time picker trigger, and checkbox indicator classes — import from `form-control-styles.ts`; do not duplicate hover/filled rings on one-off fields
- **Filled vs empty**: use `data-filled` on **Input** and **Textarea** (components sync on mount/change for RHF uncontrolled fields). **Select** wrapper sets `data-empty` / `data-has-value` via `emptyValues` prop
- **Do not** rely on `:not(:placeholder-shown)` for filled styling — inputs without `placeholder` mis-fire
- **Meaningful value**: `inputHasValue()` / `valueHasMeaningfulContent()` trim strings; whitespace-only = empty. Align with Zod `.trim()` on text fields in `lib/validation/*` where user-facing required strings matter
- **Select sentinels**: `DEFAULT_SELECT_EMPTY_VALUES` (`none`, `""`) for form fields; `FILTER_SELECT_EMPTY_VALUES` (`all`, `""`) for library/filter selects — pass `emptyValues={FILTER_SELECT_EMPTY_VALUES}` so “All types” / “All folders” do not get filled background
- **Checkbox**: custom indicator; checked = primary fill; **enabled-only** hover hint on unchecked (faint check icon, no primary fill until checked); disabled = default cursor, no hover effect (`peer` disabled overrides)
- **Errors**: `aria-invalid` + `border-destructive` on control; `text-sm text-destructive` message below; root/auth errors in `rounded-2xl` destructive alert (`AuthFormAlert` pattern)
- **Select typing**: `Select` is `SelectPrimitive.Root.Props<string>` — `onValueChange` receives `string | null`; type callbacks explicitly when needed

#### Tooltips

- Use shadcn **`Tooltip` / `TooltipTrigger` / `TooltipContent`** from `@/components/ui/tooltip` — not native `title` for rich copy
- **`TooltipProvider`** lives in `AppLayout` with `delay={300}` — do not nest extra providers unless isolating a subtree
- **Content style**: dark popover (`bg-foreground` / `text-background`), `max-w-xs`, title `font-semibold`, body `text-xs text-background/85`; optional `side="top"` `sideOffset={6–8}`
- **Examples**: `CalendarEventBlock` (calendar-week-view); **`ChainTypeOptionLabel`** for chain type checkboxes (copy from `chain-type-tooltips.ts`, dotted underline + `cursor-help`)

#### Auth pages (`/login`, `/register`)

- Use **`AuthPageShell`**, **`AuthFormCard`**, **`AuthField`**, **`AuthFooterLink`** from `components/auth/auth-page-shell.tsx` — split layout (branding column `lg+`, form column); mobile logo above form
- Register: invitation badge, read-only email with lock icon + muted bg; registration-closed state with dashed empty panel; `Suspense` fallback uses `AuthLoadingCard` inside shell

#### Dashboard

- **Admin**: `AdminHome` — live stats from `adminApi`
- **Instructor**: `InstructorHome` — placeholder stat cards (`DASHBOARD_STATS`) until APIs exist; stat links to Calendar / Exercises / Class plans; Clients “coming soon” (non-link); quick actions + optional today schedule empty state; note in UI that stats are placeholders when using static data

#### Scheduling UI

- **Calendar**: `CalendarPanel` shell (loading/error/empty); `CalendarHeader` (stats, view toggle, new class); `calendar-week-view` / `calendar-month-view`; `ClassInstanceDrawer` on instance click
- **Week overview**: `WeekOverviewPanel` — week nav, day strip (`Button` outline), day sections, `WeekClassCard` (GROUP vs PRIVATE color accents)
- **Dialogs**: `create-class-dialog`, `edit-class-dialog`, `quick-schedule-dialog` — `rounded-3xl` content; prefer **`useWatch`** over `watch()` from RHF for React Compiler compatibility

#### Libraries & pickers (UX patterns)

- **Library headers** (exercises, class plans, admin users): one header card — title, live counts (`listTotalCount ?? totalCount`), primary actions, debounced search, filters; **directory empty** vs **filtered empty** (filters active + zero results but total > 0)
- **Pagination**: always render `ExerciseLibraryPagination` under grid/list with `ariaLabel`; pass controlled `page` / `totalPages` / `onPageChange` / `loading`
- **Exercise picker dialog**: **multi-select** — checkbox per row, row click toggles selection, footer “Add N to section” batch add; do not close on single row click; **Create new** tab still creates one exercise and adds immediately

#### React / ESLint patterns (UI-related)

- Avoid **synchronous `setState` in `useEffect`** (`react-hooks/set-state-in-effect`): defer fetches/resets with `setTimeout(0)` and cleanup, or set state in the same async callback that receives data (e.g. `load()` sets detail + reschedule), or **derive** display values instead of syncing props → state (`section-exercise-fields`, template selection via `useMemo`)
- Prefer **`useWatch({ control, name })`** over `watch()` in forms
- Avoid reading **`ref.current` during render** in submit handlers — use state when values affect JSX or `handleSubmit` closures
- **Images in fancybox previews**: native `<img>` allowed with `eslint-disable-next-line @next/next/no-img-element` and a short comment — do not switch to `next/image` without testing gallery behavior

#### When improving UI

- Reuse existing composites before inventing new layouts; extend `form-control-styles`, `AuthPageShell`, `CalendarPanel`, library header patterns
- Keep diffs focused; do not restyle unrelated pages in a feature PR
- Session-wide UI changelog (reference): `CHANGELOG_SESSION.md` at repo root
- **API calls**: use the `api` helper from `@/lib/api` for generic requests; prefer typed modules in `@/services/*` (e.g. `admin-api`, `exercise-api`) for feature endpoints — all use `credentials: "include"` via the shared client; base URL from `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`
- **`exerciseApi`** (`@/services/exercise-api`): typed helpers for exercises — **`getExercises`** (unpaginated array; use from pickers / full lists without `page`), **`getExerciseListPage`** (paginated **`PaginatedExerciseList`** for the library grid), `getExerciseById`, `createExercise`, `updateExercise`, `deleteExercise`, `setProgression`, `getProgressionChain`, folder CRUD, image add/delete/reorder, temp upload/delete. Shared constants: **`EXERCISE_LIBRARY_PAGE_SIZE`** (default page size for **`getExerciseListPage`**). **`SaveExerciseBody`** includes optional `progressionOfId`, `progressionNotes`, `regressionNotes`, `equipment: string[]`, `chainType: string[]`, and `layers: { content, order?, isFinisher? }[]`. Exercise pages and forms should use this module rather than ad-hoc `api.get`/`patch` for `/exercises/*`. **Mapping**: library listing → **`getExerciseListPage`**; class-plan **`exercise-picker-dialog`** → **`getExercises`** (see Backend **Pagination design note — exercise list dual response**).
- **`classPlanApi`** (`@/services/class-plan-api`): **`listClassPlans`**, **`getClassPlanById`**, create/update/delete template, duplicate, section CRUD, section-exercise CRUD, **`getFolders`** / folder CRUD under **`/class-plan-folders`**. List params include **`page`**, **`limit`**; response **`ClassPlanListResponse`**. **`CLASS_PLAN_LIBRARY_PAGE_SIZE`** matches the library UI page size.
- **`dropdownApi`** (`@/services/dropdown-api`): `getOptions(categoryKey)` and `createOption(categoryKey, label)`. **`useDropdownOptions(key)`** hook fetches and caches options for a category; form selects consume it.
- **Exercise progression UI**: **`ProgressionChainViewer`** (`components/exercises/progression-chain-viewer.tsx`) on the exercise detail page shows Level 1 → harder steps (responsive layout, current exercise highlighted); skips rendering when the chain has fewer than two steps. **`ExerciseForm`** and **`ExerciseFormMultistep`** both include **`progressionOfId`** in the save payload (defaults to **`"none"`** → `null`). The inline **"Easier version (progression)"** `Select` is **commented out** in **`exercise-form.tsx`** and **`exercise-form-multistep.tsx`** (multistep comment block documents how to restore picker + **`getExercises`** / watch / memos). Change progression via **`exerciseApi.setProgression`** / **`PATCH /api/exercises/:id/progression`**, or re-enable the **`Controller`** block. On multistep edit, **`getProgressionChain`** still feeds **blocked parent IDs** for submit validation if the field is ever set to a disallowed parent. Stale `progressionOfId` after a soft-deleted parent is handled on the API side.
- **Exercise library page** (`exercises/page.tsx`): unified **`ExerciseLibraryHeader`** (title, live stats from **`listTotalCount ?? totalExerciseCount`**, "New folder" + "New exercise", search, folder **`Select`** with counts, Rename/Delete when a folder is selected) + **`ExerciseList`**. **`useExerciseLibrary`** composes **`useExerciseSearch`**, **`useExerciseList`**, and **`useExerciseFolders`**. **Listing is always paginated**: **`useExerciseList`** calls **`exerciseApi.getExerciseListPage`** on every load with **`page`** and **`limit: EXERCISE_LIBRARY_PAGE_SIZE`** — do not use **`getExercises`** on this page (that path is for pickers only). Filter reset to page 1 on filter change; **`refreshExercises`** promise for folder flows. Filtered-empty state uses **`listTotalCount === 0`** with active filters while **`totalExerciseCount > 0`**. Search matches **`name`** + **`description`**. **`ExerciseLibraryPagination`** is always rendered under the grid (pass **`page`**, **`totalPages`**, **`onPageChange`**, **`loading`**, **`ariaLabel`**); on a single page, prev/next stay disabled. Omit props on **`ExerciseLibraryPagination`** for the static disabled preview (e.g. docs). Same **controlled** props on **`/admin/users`**.
- **Class plans library** (`class-plans/page.tsx`): **`ClassPlanLibraryHeader`** + **`ClassPlanList`** + folder dialog; **`useClassPlanLibrary`** composes search, **`useClassPlanList`** (paginated **`listClassPlans`**, **`CLASS_PLAN_LIBRARY_PAGE_SIZE`**, page state + filter reset across folder / type / style / tag), and **`useClassPlanFolders`**. Header totals use **`listTotalCount ?? totalTemplateCount`**; filtered-empty uses **`listTotalCount === 0`**. **`ExerciseLibraryPagination`** is always rendered under the list (with **`ariaLabel`**); on a single page, prev/next stay disabled.
- **Admin users page** (`admin/users/page.tsx`): UX mirrors the exercise library — outer **`space-y-6`** + rounded page shell, single header card (title, live stats, **Invite user**, **`useDebounce`** email search with clear control), directory vs filtered **empty states** (same intent as `exercise-list`), user table + **`ExerciseLibraryPagination`** (controlled). Listing uses Better Auth **`authClient.admin.listUsers`** with pagination + optional email search. Invitations via **`adminApi.invite`**. Row actions: details sheet, role change, ban/unban via admin plugin.
- **Exercise image dropzone**: **`ExerciseForm`** and **`ExerciseFormMultistep`** use `react-dropzone` (`useDropzone`) for temp uploads; saved + temp images in one sortable list; edit path calls **`deleteImage`** / **`reorderImages`**; temp **`publicIds[]`** on save.
- **Exercise layer UI**: dynamic layer rows (add/remove); each row labeled `Layer 1`, `Layer 2`, … Only the **last** row can be **Finisher** (`ExerciseLayer.isFinisher`); adding a layer clears prior finisher; finisher badge/styling on last row. **Remove** control: **`toolbarEndSlot`** on layer **`BulletTextarea`** — shown for **Layer 2+** only (`index > 0` when more than one layer); **Layer 1** never shows remove (schema requires ≥1 layer). **`getLayerStepTitle`** in `@/lib/exercise-layer-labels` returns `Layer N` only (no automatic finisher wording).
- **`BulletTextarea`** (`components/exercises/bullet-textarea.tsx`): used in exercise forms for layer `content`, description, starting position, cueing, progression/regression notes. Bullets are literal `•` in the stored string. **Enter** / **Add •** / **`bulletsEnabled`** bullet behavior when enabled. **`bulletsEnabled={false}`**: plain **`Textarea`** plus optional **label** row and **`toolbarEndSlot`** (e.g. remove layer) in a top row with **`data-bullet-textarea-toolbar`** on the slot wrapper for focus when tabbing to toolbar controls. **`Textarea`** is `forwardRef` for selection restore after programmatic inserts.
- **`ExercisePreText`** (`components/exercises/exercise-pre-text.tsx`): read-only display on the exercise **detail** page for layer bodies and other long strings; preserves line breaks like pre-wrapped text; lines beginning with `•` get a **hanging indent** so wrapped text aligns under the text after the bullet.

### Database Models (Prisma)
- `Instructor` — identity & auth (mapped as Better Auth's `user` via `user.modelName`); has `role` (`Role` enum: `ADMIN`/`INSTRUCTOR`), `banned`, `banReason`, `banExpires`
- `Session`, `Account`, `Verification` — Better Auth managed tables
- `Invitation` — admin-created invitations with `token`, `status` (`InvitationStatus` enum: `PENDING`/`ACCEPTED`/`EXPIRED`), `role`, `expiresAt`;
- `PlatformSetting` — key-value store for platform config (e.g. `signupEnabled`)
- `ExerciseFolder`, `Exercise`, `ExerciseImage`, `ExerciseLayer` — exercise library; `Exercise` has optional **`progressionOfId`** (easier parent exercise) forming a linear progression chain per instructor; optional **`progressionNotes`** / **`regressionNotes`**; `ExerciseLayer` stores ordered content steps per exercise plus optional **`isFinisher`** on the final layer
- `DropdownCategory`, `DropdownOption` — configurable dropdown menus; categories and global defaults are seeded in `seed.ts` (exercise-related keys plus `class_type` / `class_style`); options can be global (`instructorId` null) or instructor-scoped
- `ClassPlanTemplate`, `PlanSection`, `PlanSectionExercise` — class plan templates
- `Class`, `ClassInstance` — scheduling (GROUP/PRIVATE, recurrence)
- `Client`, `Enrollment`, `Attendance` — client roster
- `SessionNote`, `SessionNoteExercise` — per-instance notes
